{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_9","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"nl -ba README_EN.md | sed -n '1,220p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\t# complex-task-orchestrator\n     2\t\n     3\tA reusable skill that pushes complex tasks through clarify, align, execute, and self-review instead of letting the model charge ahead too early.\n     4\t\n     5\t[中文说明](./README.md)\n     6\t\n     7\t## When To Use\n     8\t\n     9\t- complex, ambiguous, multi-stage tasks\n    10\t- work where misunderstanding is expensive\n    11\t- tasks that benefit from explicit consensus before execution\n    12\t- research reviews, system design, project planning, open-ended implementation, skill and workflow design\n    13\t\n    14\t## When Not To Use\n    15\t\n    16\t- tiny bug fixes\n    17\t- short rewrites\n    18\t- trivial formatting\n    19\t- single-step factual lookups\n    20\t- low-risk requests where the process would cost more than the task\n    21\t\n    22\t## 30-Second Example\n    23\t\n    24\t```text\n    25\tThis is a complex task. Use complex-task-orchestrator to clarify the requirement, confirm consensus, create an execution prompt, and then do the work.\n    26\t```\n    27\t\n    28\t```text\n    29\tUse complex-task-orchestrator to clarify this ambiguous task before execution.\n    30\t```\n    31\t\n    32\t## What Happens On First Run\n    33\t\n    34\tOn a typical first run, the skill will try to move the task through a more reliable path:\n    35\t\n    36\t1. clarify the most important ambiguity\n    37\t2. restate the requirement and ask for confirmation\n    38\t3. generate a task-specific execution document\n    39\t4. execute\n    40\t5. self-review, revise, and summarize\n    41\t\n    42\tIf the task is already clear enough, it can switch to the `Quick Path`:\n    43\t\n    44\t- 0 to 1 clarification turns\n    45\t- one short consensus confirmation\n    46\t- a short execution prompt\n    47\t- self-review still required\n    48\t\n    49\t## What A Run Usually Produces\n    50\t\n    51\tIf writing artifacts is allowed, the default minimal outputs are:\n    52\t\n    53\t- `01-requirement-consensus.md`\n    54\t- `02-task-execution-prompt.md`\n    55\t- `03-self-review-and-summary.md`\n    56\t\n    57\tSee [docs/first-run-example.md](docs/first-run-example.md) and [artifact conventions](skill/complex-task-orchestrator/references/artifact-conventions.md).\n    58\t\n    59\t## Why It Is More Reliable Than Direct Prompting\n    60\t\n    61\tDirect prompting often fails in three ways:\n    62\t\n    63\t- execution starts before the requirement is actually clear\n    64\t- the answer looks polished but solves the wrong problem\n    65\t- the task ends without a real revision loop\n    66\t\n    67\tThis skill is useful because it makes the execution contract explicit before the model commits to a path.\n    68\t\n    69\tMore detail: [docs/why-this-helps.md](docs/why-this-helps.md)\n    70\t\n    71\t## Install\n    72\t\n    73\t### Codex\n    74\t\n    75\t```bash\n    76\tbash /path/to/complex-task-orchestrator/scripts/install-codex-skill.sh\n    77\t```\n    78\t\n    79\tThis creates:\n    80\t\n    81\t```text\n    82\t~/.codex/skills/complex-task-orchestrator\n    83\t```\n    84\t\n    85\t### Claude Code\n    86\t\n    87\t```bash\n    88\tbash /path/to/complex-task-orchestrator/scripts/install-claude-code-skill.sh\n    89\t```\n    90\t\n    91\tThis creates:\n    92\t\n    93\t```text\n    94\t~/.claude/skills/complex-task-orchestrator\n    95\t```\n    96\t\n    97\tCompatibility details: [docs/claude-code-compatibility.md](docs/claude-code-compatibility.md)\n    98\t\n    99\t## Public Examples\n   100\t\n   101\t- [Examples index](docs/cases/README.md)\n   102\t- [Case 1: research review](docs/cases/case-01-research-review.md)\n   103\t- [Case 2: skill bootstrap](docs/cases/case-02-skill-bootstrap.md)\n   104\t- [Case 3: project remediation](docs/cases/case-03-project-remediation.md)\n   105\t- [before / after comparison](docs/cases/before-after-comparison.md)\n   106\t\n   107\tThese are curated public assets, not raw runtime exports. See [docs/runtime-asset-boundary.md](docs/runtime-asset-boundary.md).\n   108\t\n   109\t## Runtime Memory\n   110\t\n   111\tThis repository now includes a minimal runtime memory layer:\n   112\t\n   113\t- `runtime/captures/`\n   114\t- `runtime/promoted/patterns/`\n   115\t- `runtime/promoted/failure-modes/`\n   116\t- `runtime/state/runtime-memory-manifest.json`\n   117\t\n   118\tSpecification: [docs/runtime-memory-spec.md](docs/runtime-memory-spec.md)\n   119\tGovernance: [docs/runtime-governance.md](docs/runtime-governance.md)\n   120\t\n   121\t## Current Status\n   122\t\n   123\tAs of April 17, 2026, this project includes:\n   124\t\n   125\t- an installable skill\n   126\t- Codex and Claude Code install scripts\n   127\t- quick path and full path behavior\n   128\t- a minimal runtime memory host\n   129\t- a packaged `v0.2.0` release set\n   130\t- 3 public cases and 1 comparison page\n   131\t- changelog, smoke checklist, and validation matrix\n   132\t- a Round 2 client-validation framework\n   133\t- lightweight memory governance rules\n   134\t\n   135\tIt does not claim:\n   136\t\n   137\t- a mature automated memory system\n   138\t- complete behavior validation across all clients\n   139\t- that `.local-docs/` is the public evidence layer\n   140\t\n   141\t## Repository Structure\n   142\t\n   143\t```text\n   144\tskill/complex-task-orchestrator/\n   145\t  SKILL.md\n   146\t  references/\n   147\t  runtime/\n   148\tscripts/\n   149\t  install-codex-skill.sh\n   150\t  install-claude-code-skill.sh\n   151\t  validate-skill-project.sh\n   152\tdocs/\n   153\t  cases/\n   154\t  templates/\n   155\t  *.md\n   156\t.claude/skills/complex-task-orchestrator\n   157\t```\n   158\t\n   159\t## Maintenance Signals\n   160\t\n   161\t- [CHANGELOG.md](CHANGELOG.md)\n   162\t- [docs/releases/v0.2.0-release-notes.md](docs/releases/v0.2.0-release-notes.md)\n   163\t- [docs/smoke-checklist.md](docs/smoke-checklist.md)\n   164\t- [docs/validation-matrix.md](docs/validation-matrix.md)\n   165\t\n   166\t## License\n   167\t\n   168\tMIT\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
